From ca943cf34dd7afbe4cbcf1ad8658b7b50e965fd7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ElXreno <elxreno@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 28 Apr 2026 16:52:07 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: mac80211: allow key installation for TDLS peers before
 association

Stations added with NL80211_STA_FLAG_TDLS_PEER deliberately do not
transition through WLAN_STA_ASSOC in sta_apply_parameters(): the
existing comment states 'auth flags will be set later for TDLS, and
for unassociated stations that move to associated'. However,
ieee80211_add_key() rejects key installation for stations that are
not yet in WLAN_STA_ASSOC, unless they are Enhanced Privacy
Protection (EPP) peers.

When wpa_supplicant completes the 802.11z TPK handshake and issues
NL80211_CMD_NEW_KEY to install the TDLS pairwise key, the kernel
returns -ENOENT because the peer is still at state NONE. wpa_supplicant
logs 'nl80211: kernel reports: key addition failed' followed by
'TDLS: Failed to set TPK to the driver' and does not retry. mac80211
then moves the TDLS peer through AUTHENTICATED / ASSOCIATED /
AUTHORIZED without a working pairwise key, leaving a zombie peer
entry.

On some drivers the zombie entry corrupts BSS state. On MediaTek
MT7925 (mt76), repeated attempts progressively degrade firmware
state until userspace traffic on the main BSS link stops flowing
entirely and the only recovery is manual Wi-Fi reconnection. The
same symptom was filed against MT7922 as kernel.org bug 216421
and closed UNREPRODUCIBLE without investigation.

The WLAN_STA_ASSOC check was introduced by commit 1626e0fa740d
("mac80211: fix FT roaming") to preserve legacy behavior where
drivers expected key installation to occur after association. TDLS
peers are mutually authenticated by the 802.11z TPK handshake before
key installation is requested, so there is no integrity concern with
accepting the key for a TDLS peer at state NONE. The TODO directly
above the guard (present since 2013) describes exactly this scenario:
'accept the key if we have a station entry and add it to the device
after the station associates.'

Add sta->sta.tdls to the exemption list alongside sta->sta.epp_peer,
mirroring the exemption pattern introduced by commit 63e7e3b6433f
("wifi: mac80211: allow key installation before association") for
EPP peers.

Link: https://bugzilla.kernel.org/show_bug.cgi?id=216421
Signed-off-by: ElXreno <elxreno@gmail.com>
---
 net/mac80211/cfg.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/net/mac80211/cfg.c b/net/mac80211/cfg.c
index 00261bd6674b..0f9500039b31 100644
--- a/net/mac80211/cfg.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/cfg.c
@@ -684,7 +684,8 @@ static int ieee80211_add_key(struct wiphy *wiphy, struct wireless_dev *wdev,
 		 * TODO: accept the key if we have a station entry and
 		 *	 add it to the device after the station associates.
 		 */
-		if (!sta || (!sta->sta.epp_peer &&
+		if (!sta || (!sta->sta.tdls &&
+			     !sta->sta.epp_peer &&
 			     !test_sta_flag(sta, WLAN_STA_ASSOC))) {
 			ieee80211_key_free_unused(key);
 			return -ENOENT;
-- 
2.53.0
